skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:title: {"id": "fbbdb250-4796-4cb5-b746-c4a0b100a1c5", "value": "FISH Archaeological Objects Thesaurus"}
skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:description: {"id": "b2e7b50a-1438-47a8-ae5d-dc0caecbbbe2", "value": "Originally developed by the Archaeological Objects Working Party and published by the mda. It provides guidance for the recording of archaeological objects in Britain and Ireland covering all historical periods. Now maintained by FISH on behalf of the heritage sector"}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "81d72248-4971-4ccc-bbc7-63c50a53d6d8", "value": "A tool which combines two or more different types of tool."}
{"id": "a629aec6-5964-4806-83fc-490557446c7d", "value": "Polished bone used to burnish objects eg pottery."}
{"id": "3dca1aac-16cb-4145-8923-5edbc74ec642", "value": "A stringed instrument with a fingerboard which has frets on it."}
{"id": "0df2c4e2-a2f5-4253-8e15-4ee40ac27074", "value": "A plucked string instrument in which the strings pass over the soundbox and parallel to the sides of the instrument."}
{"id": "315307d7-dba6-427c-b98f-eb53996dd1d2", "value": "A plucked string instrument of a specific medieval / early post medieval type."}
{"id": "1397010f-46bf-459f-8a32-66af0199b827", "value": "A stringed instrument usually with a triangular frame."}
{"id": "8b325588-b609-4cb4-9a85-010f50e3dff2", "value": "An instrument played mainly by plucking the strings. Use narrower term where known."}
{"id": "c0b83d3d-6aa8-47e1-a644-5951a5dca87a", "value": "A stringed instrument with a very rounded body."}

{"id": "a7702a9e-15bc-462a-84ab-ec1c6ed63974", "value": "An end scraper which has a retouched end that is straight in form. If the tool blank is a blade or flake, and the retouch is abrupt retouch rather than scraper retouch then use either Truncated blade or Truncated flake. (Source: SARC)"}
{"id": "2dc2f264-8c79-4fe6-bab7-59b20432cebf", "value": "A fishing spear with two heads to grip fish between."}
{"id": "c265dd12-fdab-4adf-abd9-0cd87f0e31a6", "value": "An arrowhead which has a straight cutting edge."}

{"id": "d5dfa882-51bc-480f-a89a-7ad9d4838a20", "value": "A stone core which is irregular in shape. It can have numerous usuable or abandoned striking platforms. It is the most common core type and it is often the last attempt of a knapper to extract the final usable flakes form the core. (Source: SARC)"}
{"id": "e0e4a291-f7d7-44ac-9e07-b2b8c38014cb", "value": "Thick material, usually woven, used as a covering for the floor."}
{"id": "bb3e0d9d-6d47-44ed-ae2d-aa02fc7fd772", "value": "A container for holy relics."}
{"id": "50bd8f45-be9e-4694-9e04-1c97b3050938", "value": "A cross connected to a reliquary or containing a relic itself."}
{"id": "b9b0136c-48e4-4d64-8a5d-3e8981520bf4", "value": "A small narrow pointed missile that is thrown or shot."}
{"id": "4c9fc47e-8da6-4bdc-8e96-418e16bdc18b", "value": "A structure consecrated for devotional purposes."}
{"id": "be4855e2-a475-4b23-937c-a095a42cd7c6", "value": "A block on which objects are chopped or cut."}
{"id": "deda78f6-83db-408d-bd32-9cbeba05b2cf", "value": "The blade or sharp-pointed head attached to the end of a spear's shaft."}
{"id": "c24776b9-8384-4846-89ab-347d4f938757", "value": "A long handled weapon which has a long blade in line with the shaft, sharpened on both sides and ending in a point."}
{"id": "2d1b627a-c947-4821-9667-6e857a5fb29a", "value": "Military weapon with long shaft and bill style head. For agricultural style bills use bill hook."}
{"id": "8a7b113b-9ea2-436a-99d3-c06b7af752e8", "value": "A long shaft topped by an axe head. Differs from a battleaxe by the length of the shaft."}
{"id": "56db5415-52b0-465e-b797-62c5b181dab4", "value": "A long shafted weapon with a head that can be edged and/or pointed."}
{"id": "8021e18b-0e4d-4b8e-bb2a-4dc4aa447ede", "value": "A weapon which is a blade fixed to a long handle."}
{"id": "78d06174-c578-45c4-b820-06086d886224", "value": "A long shafted weapon with a pointed head used for thrusting or as a missile."}
{"id": "ce84d750-c744-4696-850d-de429915210a", "value": "A combination of spear and axe on a long handle."}
{"id": "74a1aa9f-8acf-4d0d-a881-8bb7b3f47047", "value": "A weapon with a long shaft and a three pronged head."}

{"id": "0170ff2c-ee8e-4ab5-be06-08a7b317d16d", "value": "A core which has two opposing platforms. One end serving as the main platform for the removal of blades - the other being used to straighten the face of the core and correct knapping errors. Removals are taken from the full circumference. (Source: SARC)"}
{"id": "467e5944-9cf3-496b-aa27-a71f5f8fa598", "value": "A receptacle used as a home for bees, traditionally made of thick straw work in the shape of a dome,but sometimes made of wood."}
{"id": "4c746fd5-e788-47a2-9dae-97d1f378b374", "value": "A portable beehive, often made of straw."}
{"id": "76f158bf-5265-4421-8b82-c8b541a59834", "value": "An tool used to separate flax fibres from the wood and bark following retting."}
{"id": "1692caf4-4b5e-4321-9c5e-ca6bbe363ec2", "value": "A tool for cleaning a person's nails."}
{"id": "fb80d201-36c6-4278-9111-0a5e33405b26", "value": "A piece of fabric for wiping the nose, face or hands."}
{"id": "cb1656b2-e97d-4d24-af35-05cebf2352b8", "value": "The barrel of a feather, usually goose, used as a pen."}
{"id": "94e6052a-bda4-4cbb-853b-198f5545636c", "value": "A plug to keep out dust, moisture etc."}
{"id": "06f40386-6033-4614-83c5-35b351897011", "value": "An instrument with a series of pipes at different pitches, the air being produced by bellows, and pipes selected by keyboard or sliders."}
{"id": "7acc556b-e571-4615-9fe2-5a35e7879104", "value": "A carved head of Iron Age or Roman date, with uncertain use."}
{"id": "66a9da4a-d474-4b4f-9be9-dfa42a858a73", "value": "A prepared core from which a single flake or blade has been produced. The technique was primarily used in the Palaeolithic and Neolithic."}
{"id": "3dc823bc-58ea-4557-94cb-3bc2b2c33734", "value": "A small hand operated rotary drill used by dentists."}
{"id": "5f51cae4-7bad-4bcc-97aa-5ba58f63f618", "value": "Tool used in dentistry either for examination or surgery."}
{"id": "fc74c0d0-c250-4c61-870b-dcce23d7f2f4", "value": "Wind-blown silt."}

{"id": "6d0fb18b-c063-4f44-9cdf-dfddde953b61", "value": "A long, thin cane of glass made by layering glass of various colours in a mould and pulling the soft glass until the cane was of the desired thickness. When cut and viewed in section the cane has a mosaic like appearance."}
{"id": "b433353e-6f7d-4381-a66c-552f1ef004a8", "value": "A bench with a back, usually in a church."}
{"id": "b4e8aaa7-cba5-4e34-a01e-78fef106ccc5", "value": "An object to sit upon. Use narrower terms where known."}
{"id": "8c922eff-fcb7-475d-b030-f55dc9fdbef4", "value": "A single seat with a back, sometimes also arms."}
{"id": "c4e8788f-44ef-4121-a683-d7ac1a239c34", "value": "A long seat usually without a back."}
{"id": "0824c8f0-7ae7-4f38-b1e1-34718fe1bc08", "value": "A projection on the under side of a hinged choir stall seat providing support during long periods of standing."}
{"id": "69aadc02-ff2a-4307-ab41-d484ee1ebce0", "value": "A long seat for reclining on."}
{"id": "1ea13d75-a077-4aa8-b28e-40471781fb47", "value": "A small type of seat, usually without a back, set on legs."}
{"id": "86d6c65a-e907-477f-9f54-593ab3cda671", "value": "A case for the transportation and protection of musical instruments."}
{"id": "13e35613-1989-46c2-a541-2d1ddc87c846", "value": "Use more specific term where available."}
{"id": "4e8db739-d565-4b8d-98ec-31006e41ad94", "value": "A flat surface supported by legs used for many purposes."}
{"id": "09c7368a-b2d0-46c4-a43e-faff59671a30", "value": "A low stool for resting feet upon."}
{"id": "0abc3284-1a23-4481-8abf-93a6c8f9865c", "value": "A polished reflective surface."}
{"id": "aea891f8-ebd6-4b5f-a01a-1dea3ade276d", "value": "A piece of furniture containing a chamber pot or wash basin."}
{"id": "1a4a67b6-ae78-46fc-b9ed-3fff8968a0c0", "value": "The cover for a garderobe on which a person would sit."}
{"id": "b94134ad-d45c-40cd-8f59-3ad0a84892fd", "value": "A child's bed, usually without rockers."}
{"id": "4e68ebc9-6265-428c-8a3e-95b88920db9b", "value": "A piece of furniture with one or more doors concealing storage space."}
{"id": "aa70a9a9-1c01-4df1-8003-cafe4fe2454e", "value": "To be used for the frame elements only, not for the bedding."}
{"id": "4c87848a-8328-4b76-9c51-00fcdf3a317f", "value": "A box used for storage or shipping."}
{"id": "bcf98145-55fa-4b7a-9277-8e44d3c68598", "value": "A child's bed, usually with rockers."}
{"id": "0592b98e-eccb-4143-b032-1ec30fa1a19d", "value": "A portable writing-case or surface, especially one for use on the lap. May contain compartments for storing writing materials and paper."}
{"id": "06177f69-9a76-4aff-9201-46f41a52ab30", "value": "A piece of furniture containing shelves, cupboards or drawers for storage or display."}
{"id": "98c2e006-b0ee-4197-9b19-6092bf16d5ec", "value": "A piece of furniture intended to hold drinks, side dishes etc."}
{"id": "b9298af5-4037-4d6b-8280-f440ba44560f", "value": "Movable, usually functional, articles in a room. Use only for objects believed to be furniture where more specific term is not identifiable."}
{"id": "416aff8e-3893-423d-9cdd-d50a45600dfc", "value": "A piece of strengthened material worn projecting over the forehead and eyes to provide shade for the eyes."}
{"id": "be8644cf-ec89-45f1-a11e-ca63ae416fb2", "value": "A form of hat, usually does not cover the forehead nor have a brim, and usually worn by women."}
{"id": "65bf9aca-eae8-464c-a342-3d0ca923e3b8", "value": "Light material used to cover the face or head."}
{"id": "e586c478-b96e-4b26-a28c-021020d3c0e1", "value": "A covering for the head with a peak to shade the eyes."}
{"id": "b6b52fd0-8aca-40ef-b0a5-f4517328ecaa", "value": "A net worn over the hair to hold it in place."}
{"id": "39dd691d-eded-4953-924d-59abcb6d0b99", "value": "A pad of cloth or fur for keeping the ears warm."}
{"id": "5f1dc9df-1cc2-414c-90ef-719b9fa75ad6", "value": "Headwear where a band of material is wound around a cap."}
{"id": "611c6e47-7156-47ef-b899-8f0fc1ad9f4a", "value": "A piece of cloth worn over the head."}
{"id": "feb5326e-66b4-4ae6-8dae-4c7d74d36565", "value": "A cloth or scarf worn over the head as a covering."}
{"id": "f13ba134-b0cf-47bf-a749-9b06c8060e6c", "value": "An artifical head of hair worn to disguise baldness, for adornment, for ceremonial or theatrical use etc."}
{"id": "83e84a90-d148-4f94-a94b-0b0b547983a3", "value": "A band of cloth or other material worn around the head, not totally covering it."}
{"id": "465cbf48-62c2-414c-8244-9a2cd146abaa", "value": "A head cover which can be attached to a piece of outerwear, eg a coat, or can be separate."}
{"id": "9761e2d6-7530-41b2-917f-cbedffcef8c7", "value": "Covering for the head, especially ornamental."}
{"id": "c1628a46-29d8-4901-a021-d6c60aef8272", "value": "An object worn on the head."}
{"id": "76acdb66-d375-485a-941a-7dcd08bf5296", "value": "A wig, toupee or section of extra hair designed to replace or enhance the wearer's real hair giving greater quantity, bulk or length."}
{"id": "719b74a3-2097-42c9-8a44-a6a849ebae12", "value": "A fine net worn over the hair."}
{"id": "d3d07079-1b91-44ef-88a9-1b43ef2ee4aa", "value": "A head covering, usually with a brim."}
{"id": "b9c51a42-b2d5-48b1-9665-94892ee986bf", "value": "A specific form of cauldron, generally of rounded profile made in the Low Countries. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "e7058d27-368d-44bd-ab9e-c8bd7d2fc663", "value": "A large pot used for boiling."}

{"id": "61ce7af5-f412-4b41-b965-cf21467ba6d8", "value": "A small notebook formed from two tablets usually made of wood, bone, ivory or metal. They were given as commemorative gift by a consul on his installation and often decorated with the image of the consul."}

{"id": "63cb6058-3986-4ffd-a0bf-4e542fd6f0db", "value": "Roman, mid-1st century AD two-piece Bow Brooch, derived from the Colchester Brooch, with a winged, transverse head protecting a spring mechanism held by a rear facing hook over the chord, its profile evoking a leaping dolphin."}

{"id": "33eee290-9ed5-4fbb-a650-37668035efc7", "value": "Imported Roman brooch with a wide, highly arched flat backed bow, one end rolled forward onto the head to form a hinge for the the pin. Named for the head inscription assumed to be a maker's name. Dated to first half of 1st entury AD."}

{"id": "e06a4bd2-00ce-4144-97aa-59c586d45fbc", "value": "A two-piece Bow Brooch, derived from the Colchester Brooch, dating from the later first and second centuries AD and so called due to the decorative stud on the upper bow."}

{"id": "da0ef773-161a-4850-bc01-7d2c32158bc9", "value": "A Roman Bow Brooch dating from the mid-second to mid-third centuries AD, characterized by the pronounced curvature of the bow, resembling a knee. Usually used by military personnel."}

{"id": "546a6635-0c1c-468f-8e12-63ed25923c83", "value": "Any brooch with the pin sprung or hinged at one end and the catchplate at the other end of a curved or flat bow. Can be one or two piece construction."}

{"id": "27e0a20b-d8b9-4c28-8d21-29b4b596e5e6", "value": "A simple, one-piece Bow Brooch with a spring of four coils, sometimes less, its chord tucked beneath its head and variations to bow and catchplate. Dating from the first century AD."}

{"id": "60222959-5483-445b-8377-bcf89da8167c", "value": "Roman bow brooch, dating from the third to fifth centuries AD, with a P-shaped profile and a characteristic crossbar, often adorned with knobs at its end and on the head. Shown in contemporary illustrations as being worn by high ranking males."}

{"id": "7d8dd894-f4e9-47b6-ada4-b3facaf99263", "value": "1st or 2nd century Bow Brooch derived from the Colchester. It typically has a pin hinged on a bar held in a cylindrical crossbar, the bow tapering and commonly decorated. Developed examples often have a headloop and enamelled panels."}

{"id": "a0897c19-9f18-4a48-8639-e0dd142a05b6", "value": "A mid-1st century AD brooch influenced by the Thistle type, commonly with projections on the upper bow and widening to a triangular plate, often described as a fantail, below."}

{"id": "68a4df95-3cbb-4e22-aee7-a53315744ea0", "value": "Roman, mid to late 1st century, hinged Bow Brooch, related to the Aucissa Brooch, with side knobs on the upper bow, the curvature of which is confined to the brooch's top half, the lower half being straight. Frequently tinned to give a silver appearance."}

{"id": "c54e3210-925d-4b17-b5d0-41cb9ed5293a", "value": "A first century AD one-piece bow brooch, one end of which is drawn out to form a spring and pin, characterized by its long, narrow, tapering bow, a small crossbar in front of the spring and a forward hook which holds the spring chord."}

{"id": "60b5ffc6-5882-4d5a-8a7b-1cb43ae2e946", "value": "Anglo-Saxon two-piece bow brooch, dating from the 8th to 9th centuries AD, so named for the distinctive bow shaped like the arching body of a caterpillar."}

{"id": "8af07cc4-bceb-4824-bcf2-659ab1b5979b", "value": "Bow Brooch derived from the Colchester type in the mid to late 1st and 2nd centuries AD. Typically the spring is held in a semi-cylindrical crossbar with closed ends and holding the axial bar and a hook or lug on the head to hold the chord."}

{"id": "12ad1762-acdf-4fa0-8c80-a67969759e96", "value": "Early to mid-1st century AD Bow Brooch with a P-shaped profile, a cylindrical or semi-cylindrical spring cover and a round or lozenge-shaped centre plate with a short bow above and a flat leg below, both of which are reeded like the Langton Down Brooch."}

{"id": "92833229-9ef8-4003-b2c6-f8967475cf82", "value": "A Roman Bow Brooch, dating from the later 1st and 2nd centuries often worn in pairs with a linking chain. Characterized by its distinctive head, sometimes enamelled, and resembling the mouth of a trumpet."}

{"id": "34684a1a-9aac-4174-a912-d33063b74461", "value": "A two-piece Bow Brooch dating from the early to mid-first century AD in Britain, originating in Gaul. Featuring a wide flat reeded bow, this and the Thistle Brroch were the first to conceal the spring mechanism with a cylindrical or semi-cylindrical hood."}

{"id": "e3e5f9ac-321e-4383-b63d-455f5622e2f5", "value": "A Roman brooch dating from approximately 50 to 150 AD. Derived from the earlier Aesica Brooch, and fitted with a hinged pin, the body widens to a triangular plate below the bow."}
{"id": "f4373be6-fa98-4dec-a4b6-76ae70a75c50", "value": "A curfew consisting of a half section of an inverted bowl. The form has been adapted for use against a wall. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "e9d5064f-f455-4d70-b42d-97bdee393cc3", "value": "A long narrow two edged sword with a guarded hilt, used as a thrusting weapon."}
{"id": "1df03fc7-7525-4336-b4ce-29af296a0c4c", "value": "A shackle for the hand."}
{"id": "1362619d-72a3-4f42-9c31-8a71f3803e44", "value": "A restraining ring usually linked to another."}
{"id": "99bde9eb-7ef9-47f6-8f75-8c9577d55821", "value": "A shackle for the feet."}
{"id": "98dbe372-1f41-4f6c-a888-ee587d9605c6", "value": "A circular flask with one or two flattened faces. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "00d5e074-6beb-4a95-9232-891ff843c694", "value": "A bottle with a narrow neck used for wine, oil etc."}
{"id": "012c3e83-47cd-4b08-8545-ee8e0be42795", "value": "A flask with a hollow ring-shaped form. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "770b0989-e7c3-44ad-a24c-1caeeda0cc7f", "value": "A flask with a rounded, almost spherical shape. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "d4f2c8d2-e0a2-42ba-be9a-47103e124631", "value": "A hook to join parts of clothing together."}
{"id": "f8f3c933-2c2b-4d65-ad82-2e423af00c3f", "value": "A projecting stud which fastens into a socket."}
{"id": "b0036dc4-4bd7-4824-a461-b6e84b551a5f", "value": "Clasp for fastening together two loose ends."}
{"id": "355b2a4f-5814-4ef4-99bf-021eb60137aa", "value": "A strip of material, leather etc used to hold two sides of an object together."}
{"id": "7331ba8f-7b9f-45b6-9e26-dee8bb78f5cd", "value": "An item used to fasten a cloak either to another garment or to itself."}
{"id": "0e603827-8215-499b-9d6e-680f4656d61b", "value": "Any form of fastener used to fasten a girdle together."}
{"id": "7985cd56-6608-4483-a971-c143d834bbfd", "value": "A stud used for fastening an item usually used for clothing."}
{"id": "8abc92ab-4a3d-420c-b155-8c00a33a3670", "value": "An item used to join together clothing (includes footwear)."}
{"id": "4e393298-fab2-45ac-aea1-220259ad377e", "value": "A clasp on a cope."}
{"id": "3a001284-125b-4165-b64f-3cd161a53e17", "value": "A decorative clasp to fix sleeve cuffs together."}
{"id": "ee5e0c0f-8d95-4f26-b972-e4b583e098a1", "value": "A small object designed to hold together the two ends of a cuff."}
{"id": "e7380d23-16d4-4653-bd5e-987ed7189aa7", "value": "The fittings or parts on a strap."}
{"id": "b6e65992-90ae-4add-984e-ad5053ad3c71", "value": "A small hole for a lace, cord or hook to be passed through."}
{"id": "2b0ea354-53fa-4e24-82bd-eac2c15c0934", "value": "A pin worn to hold two or more pieces of material together, often when being worn as clothing."}
{"id": "59a64d8b-d7d1-471d-896c-a4aef7c0f6b5", "value": "Any form of fastener used to fasten clothing together."}
{"id": "90051568-c0cb-4a10-a7ae-5a3dbc73643b", "value": "An object which fastens cross ways."}
{"id": "b11a33ce-c04b-4748-bd5e-6027be7cc7ca", "value": "An object designed to be the end of a lace or simimlar to aid the insertion of the lace through a loop or eyelet."}
{"id": "fbc62948-258f-4a95-a4c9-e90e2c30e2bc", "value": "A circular frame or disc arranged to revolve on an axle and used to facilitate the motion of a vehicle."}
{"id": "d467ba10-8a39-4c7c-8844-0c8d3bd6a8ce", "value": "A type of fabric often used to trim clothing."}
{"id": "4424fdd2-2d88-4401-8e60-1890ff417a2c", "value": "Woven material."}
{"id": "5360f608-9bca-4992-aed0-a030ab7a5eb3", "value": "A woven fabric used to trim clothes."}
{"id": "a25d3a2b-d46a-414f-a51b-c9a6f4889287", "value": "A toothed, handled tool used to drag objects either to gather them together eg grass or hay, or to level them out eg sand or earth."}
{"id": "3a002b1f-8c6b-4af1-a28e-a1eedb32c9fa", "value": "A tap inserted into a barrel to allow liquid to be drawn from it."}
{"id": "8465d001-5dbf-4c43-a9b6-4e11a5b8b2fa", "value": "An object used to aid pouring a substance through a small opening."}
{"id": "2d70529b-7833-4126-9bca-1d9847adedaf", "value": "A tube, cyclinder or similar casing enclosing the mechanism of a pump."}
{"id": "5c936a32-34fb-4398-974d-94e60040beb1", "value": "A flexible pipe, usually fixed to a pump or tap, for the conveying of water."}

{"id": "8d4bf24a-9053-4b9e-b382-52cde1ec9ffa", "value": "Tools and equipment with a specific function and those for which a function cannot be assigned with any degree of certainty. Where the function is known, the term is also included under the relevant Class."}
{"id": "b2c8a9a0-3f9e-4c0d-ad2d-f78fe12c7918", "value": "Equipment used to pierce or puncture other objects through the use of a point."}

{"id": "e45ebea9-7a05-4344-bab6-2eb158020883", "value": "A reinforced and padded item of clothing designed to protect the upper body in sports associated with physical contact or possible injury from sporting equipment. For military uses use BREASPLATE."}
{"id": "499e351b-d9a3-4593-92ff-cdf90cf0d561", "value": "A piece of fabric with a design, used as an emblem for military or naval purposes, signalling, decoration, display, propaganda etc."}
{"id": "06676277-4564-4f1a-a106-e6dea08be57e", "value": "A flag bearing a device, often carried on two poles or hanging from a cross piece. Usually used in processions."}
{"id": "c1082b4b-f371-4091-b72c-e0aa8b574e59", "value": "A piece of material, eg metal, cloth, leather etc, added to a button to enhance or embellish it."}
{"id": "c37f2af7-1f44-4417-9ea1-b363327a265c", "value": "Armour designed to protect the leg or parts of the leg. For specific foot protection use FOOT GUARD"}
{"id": "6173bbe0-62bd-4a81-9514-4f283029da5b", "value": "An object which has been rejected eg due to being misshapen, spoilt etc."}

{"id": "1e2a2919-d143-4ca2-bcfb-ebf1cdb99196", "value": "A musket where a wheel on the lock is wound back and when the trigger is pulled the wheel moves dragging pieces of iron pyrites over the lock tocreate sparks and set powder in the pan off and so firing the main charge."}

{"id": "ab7d36bb-d71c-4fe8-adcb-462bc7775df0", "value": "A musket fired by a piece of burning match being held in the lock which, when the trigger was pulled, would contact with powder in the pan to set off the charge."}

{"id": "47f5cc66-1caf-41af-86ce-a7229a23af2f", "value": "A musket fired by use of a flintlock. A gunflint is held in the lock which on pulling the trigger pushes back the pan cover creating sparks which set off the powder in the pan causing a flame to go through and set off the charge in the barrel."}
{"id": "06a49799-7923-427a-8525-0f1822c77e76", "value": "A heavy, smooth bore, long barrelled weapon, fired from the shoulder."}
{"id": "a502e931-ccf2-421d-8788-f56dd02b9837", "value": "A musket with a snaphance lock. This lock consisted of a flint and steel but the pan cover was separate to the steel unlike the flintlock."}
{"id": "5b6a6477-408f-41f3-a97b-e721a6ccb3d9", "value": "A freestanding pole, stake etc often used to support a superstructure."}
{"id": "3f8ba484-a003-462b-b2ef-306e14751ae3", "value": "A protective covering to a drain."}
{"id": "ea18d6c0-bd2d-461a-bda1-68d5bb2a26ed", "value": "The spanning of an opening without the use of a lintel."}
{"id": "9e2b1c81-52c9-4fe8-a5b7-364bbbb14862", "value": "A fitting incorporating a series of overlapping flaps providing ventilation or transmission of sound."}
{"id": "a4593304-7714-4c5b-bdb4-af7948219aaa", "value": "The vertical recessed face of a pediment, often decorated with sculpture."}
{"id": "c38e0c9b-5665-4e88-acaa-e16886ddca3e", "value": "A wedge shaped stone used in an arch."}
{"id": "9d42a14e-e43b-4372-b54c-9577eac839d1", "value": "An architectural ornament usually surmounting the apex of a gable, canopy or roof."}
{"id": "25549971-bcb8-41bf-a07a-1e8b8a432486", "value": "A shaft sunk into the ground to reach the water level."}

{"id": "0e8cfecc-d6a9-43b8-a296-2a9e8e95e955", "value": "A carved or moulded decorative projection adorning an object or, in the case of architectural features, the termination of a moulding or the intersection of ribs or beams."}
{"id": "40482477-94d8-4cc5-8285-6401ceaea287", "value": "One of several stones used to raise a farm building, such as a granary, above the ground surface."}
{"id": "bbf420bb-b149-4a65-82ec-292342f91675", "value": "The lower surface of a room."}
{"id": "df365e7c-4941-402e-8162-6cc57d7f2c93", "value": "A detached vertical structure acting as support to a superstructure. Where a pillar is a separate monument, use a monument type thesaurus."}
{"id": "4ae3fccd-7b81-4e07-b894-27c211fee98d", "value": "An ornamental decoration which projects from the surface it is part of."}
{"id": "e72f77e2-1182-431d-8eb1-6e71523e91b4", "value": "Parts of a building's fabric, structures and associated services, eg drain pipe. If the structure is complete use a monument type thesaurus."}
{"id": "3ec58da6-4087-4f86-9298-e612be91cf09", "value": "A long vertical pillar usually of stone used as a structural support in buildings often artistically sculpted or shaped."}
{"id": "e1c6a96b-ad34-402a-9975-aac3941aeb3b", "value": "The vertical side of a window, archway, doorway or fireplace."}

{"id": "a3af6451-bb2d-4cf3-95d4-30325f7b7d44", "value": "A flat level structure, can be part of a series, used to allow a person to move from one level to another, or can occur singularly on a threshold."}
{"id": "b236a9e0-bc67-4b06-be5a-4d418c40063a", "value": "The base to a door or window frame or of a wall."}

{"id": "6b491e14-6c5f-463e-bb28-9434b8582836", "value": "The impost, or point at which a vault rests upon its support, and from which it seems to spring. Hence the term describes the bottom stone of a vault, which lies on the impost."}
{"id": "c4241d7c-655a-4590-8186-d25b444e67f5", "value": "An opening within a structure to allow air and light in and or to allow a sight outside or inside."}
{"id": "7da1ba3a-808f-4248-99df-85a710469442", "value": "The upper part of a column or pier."}
{"id": "a6d08013-fc18-4265-9f15-0ede56e87917", "value": "A spout allowing water to spill away from a building. Usually carved in images of animals, people or grotesques."}
{"id": "2ac14f29-e17c-4b7e-8140-e7602d66b3d9", "value": "A screen used to decorate or protect an opening."}
{"id": "1ab4f0d6-a028-42fb-bb97-44460a371f1e", "value": "A vertical pillar or post, often shaped."}
{"id": "00248869-d347-489b-a9a8-088baba8255e", "value": "A barrier used to close an opening, usually hinged and often hung within a supporting frame."}
{"id": "4df5c556-7240-43e3-8497-21c48e550e59", "value": "A tube for the transport of liquids and gases eg for drainage purposes."}
{"id": "f635f6bf-ffe0-4040-8e88-2c6d9d3b3663", "value": "A square or cylindrical pipe at the top of a chimney which helps the draught of air."}
{"id": "81089ffc-f974-4ae1-8098-7eb31665dace", "value": "A shallow channel to collect rain water, attached to the eaves of a building."}
{"id": "386fdb94-562c-4752-96bb-a57e0eddf270", "value": "A metal or wooden framework suspended within an opening in an external wall, fence, hedge etc, to allow ingress or egress."}
{"id": "bb4f4b2d-4045-4b56-a682-3db40c84eff1", "value": "A load carrying horizontal structural member."}
{"id": "6e8a0705-81f1-4efd-948e-6f73bd5df850", "value": "A horizontal beam over an opening to support a wall."}
{"id": "fa7b45dc-61fc-48d5-a2c1-ea3ccc23d129", "value": "A support projecting from a wall."}
{"id": "8ff93f25-6fd8-4ce3-a989-1fe1970dedc9", "value": "A support for an arch, lintel, beam etc."}
{"id": "efcc533d-26f3-4d49-92b5-eeb13b42a4fe", "value": "A piece of metal or timber holding two elements together."}
{"id": "a37b8480-f3c4-4db9-86f8-c11cf30c72b3", "value": "An individual section of panelling. Can form fences, ceilings, an outer layer to a wall etc."}
{"id": "68867c60-0114-4291-9cba-8ddfbd93e081", "value": "A vertical structure used to draw off smoke from a fire."}
{"id": "71cbf89a-0832-48c6-9b60-caed51ec4d05", "value": "The top stone of an arch which holds it all in place."}
{"id": "994fb4f4-77b2-415b-856a-79b9d6b2576e", "value": "A garment worn from the waist down by women."}
{"id": "74a4865f-4f2c-481c-85a4-1592febed501", "value": "A band of leather, cloth etc worn usually around the waist to support clothing, carry weapons, pouches, tools etc or as a decoration."}
{"id": "9d32ebbd-4005-49ff-93b1-24b3b6c4f198", "value": "A close fitting cap covering the sides, back and top of the head."}
{"id": "6718bfd4-be10-4b47-b905-a1f8436751bb", "value": "A staff used in divination."}
{"id": "6cf7fc53-b714-4e9b-872b-4b51ac5f3eaa", "value": "A piece of bone used for divination."}
{"id": "79a48fa8-cc74-4747-9f1b-2c1c8c375003", "value": "A papal document."}
{"id": "434c65a4-3f76-41a6-8d5c-81175464ee60", "value": "A bag containing food hung around a horse's head."}
{"id": "731ed140-04b1-4ad9-a95e-158082471035", "value": "A small pin or stud worn in the lapel, often decorative."}
{"id": "f78f3469-1f43-482c-97d3-31198d56b4b7", "value": "A weight used with letter scales for weighing letters or parcels and establishing the required postal rate."}
{"id": "7e78ff50-cce5-425f-8741-e1c9b5c58383", "value": "An urn containing a cremation burial."}
{"id": "3634b32b-ee1c-4b89-9326-013a23860b47", "value": "A vessel for keeping the ashes of the dead after cremation."}
{"id": "1669d14d-3b3a-42d9-b749-c2841611b40e", "value": "The burnt remains of a corpse."}
{"id": "0ddd28e8-723f-4b26-801d-531a434334d3", "value": "A long pillow, especially one used as an under pillow."}
{"id": "48870b56-2d22-435a-92d4-6f5e2b696fe8", "value": "A fragment of the body of a vessel, or hollow object, usually of ceramic or glass. If known, use specific vessel type."}
{"id": "279aba68-49ee-425a-84f6-8777b942a1a6", "value": "Use specific form where known."}
{"id": "ea2ced93-ecb6-457b-8b54-54f96540b1f3", "value": "Movable stand for carrying a body to its grave."}
{"id": "a4ae9319-2bd6-4e9a-8b55-61b1671b4a4e", "value": "A trumpet type of instrument made from or in imitation of an animal horn."}

{"id": "dab7fbca-e7d8-4993-9c62-1ca62889fd79", "value": "A metal, shankless bit, with a ring on either side used to control an animal (usually a horse) by exerting direct pressure on the tongue, lips and the side of the mouth."}
{"id": "07f7f5fc-c97f-4267-b932-b31571e0b158", "value": "A shaped and or carved stone."}
{"id": "adbbc02f-2c32-463d-97ff-b71222ca2565", "value": "A mould in which an ingot is made."}
{"id": "f157d262-cd7d-4197-a4f0-8e74fd2edeb5", "value": "A projectile or group of projectiles fired from a weapon, usually solid rather than explosive."}
{"id": "b44becb9-eda4-4a12-95c3-04287b010ba8", "value": "A solid, spherical projectile, originally made of stone but later iron."}
{"id": "f1b35cdc-8353-437e-93c0-56f260066e4a", "value": "A number of small iron balls, each about the size of a cricket ball, often numbering nine, wired together and bound in a canvas bag."}
{"id": "5e5f5e0a-c967-4a37-abee-7b44e55be1c6", "value": "A pair of cannon balls joined by a chain."}
{"id": "5148416a-b19a-43ab-b559-ad8064475294", "value": "A pair of cannon balls joined by a solid bar."}
{"id": "04de863c-c2bd-4f59-b67f-8707fe560045", "value": "A distinguishing emblem or mark, often worn to signify membership, achievement, employment etc."}
{"id": "4b9e307a-d67e-4bbe-9e44-2b6ac12cb277", "value": "A small piece of metal or other material used to hold objects together."}
{"id": "29af4a28-b1a1-4a90-aac2-5209ab7c50e7", "value": "A metal pin with two arms which is passed through a hole and held in place by the springing apart of the arms."}
{"id": "bb9d80b1-6324-4bc1-a73b-e935491a2f52", "value": "A stone used for divination."}
{"id": "bcd3b341-3bbb-4ef9-9d92-e15387d5541c", "value": "A stone inscribed or marked with runes."}
{"id": "422fdb82-c02e-45c6-887d-5c239f0fa603", "value": "A blank for a knife that has not been hammered out."}
{"id": "66013b4f-8d55-4b5f-9ffa-9c023d5c90a4", "value": "A pattern cut out in wood or metal to help shape something accurately or to reproduce shapes."}
{"id": "14dc7df3-bf1f-4417-89a4-32d58c565a73", "value": "An intially worked object, prepared to be made into a final product."}
{"id": "d1ab4b4c-3ae3-4a46-871b-c0bc4d9543fe", "value": "A secondary or incidental product of a process."}
{"id": "a49bd777-ee75-4c12-8d0d-32e6f195b55b", "value": "An example from which another object is made."}
{"id": "9f21e076-ce21-4fb7-9c78-441a0bab9f25", "value": "A piece of iron cut from blooms and lengths of bar, probably for transportation, which were then reworked."}

{"id": "0040f809-00f0-4bd5-8261-1efcd05e50c7", "value": "Low-grade cast iron in the form of balls or spheres, produced in small workshops and exported across the North Sea and Baltic region. Particularly associated with 16th century Sweden. Also spelt \"oszemundt\" and other variants."}

{"id": "e4f9409a-c032-4e64-819f-f52bc7d5bed2", "value": "Objects used in, or which are created as part of, a manufacturing or production process, including the by-products of such processes. This does not include finished items, these will appear in other appropriate classes."}
{"id": "d92a2e63-3509-48dc-a5c7-4f96c5171f48", "value": "Piece of work to test eventual pattern, sometimes small and used as a demonstration of crafter's skill."}

{"id": "4ef2d209-eae1-41b7-bbaa-e0e9383f3ea8", "value": "A piece of metal or wood, or other material used in the manufacture of an item, intended for further fabrication and therefore representing an unfinished object. Usually relates to objects manufactured in quantity such as coins, knives etc."}
{"id": "ecac5d1f-90a1-44d6-b2fc-40e967dae2c4", "value": "The original pattern/type of an object."}
{"id": "85d782e3-c90e-459a-9b07-b3f1fa199834", "value": "Molluscs found in terrestrial habitats as opposed to fresh or brackish water."}
{"id": "34c5dcfd-28a5-4bbf-bec9-6027bcd55d1e", "value": "An object used with cosmetics."}
{"id": "1a314e5f-85ee-4543-873b-e43f61e14ce6", "value": "This includes all articles created to be used for personal care, hygiene, grooming and cosmetic activities."}
{"id": "60008f2f-14cf-4196-b56e-eec906a69a14", "value": "An item used in caring for the body for appearance and cleanliness."}
{"id": "e9c7ad48-7d9e-438e-a275-93988ba137c7", "value": "A container for incense."}
{"id": "cee56b98-e043-41e2-aa52-8501e36e079b", "value": "A vessel in which incense is burnt."}

{"id": "006ea3c8-0d07-45a7-9147-47fd7271e56f", "value": "A covering of thin copper plates secured, on top of a layer of tar and horsehair, to the bottom of wooden ships to protect the hull against weeds, barnacles and especially Teredo navalis, a wood-boring worm prevalent in tropical seas."}
{"id": "a0bff49d-dd28-49a5-a6d4-a1a13aa85de5", "value": "A cord or handle which rings a bell when pulled."}
{"id": "13a90479-6223-4050-8996-f5abde29ee42", "value": "A metal, stone or wooden projection with a flat upper surface to support a shelf, arch, statue etc."}
{"id": "22ce7f7c-281b-43e9-87c5-a2db8b8908e7", "value": "A fitting of unknown function. Use more specific type where known."}
{"id": "a10d724a-e710-47dc-807d-b9a2d2fb49b7", "value": "An object attached to a window which is removable."}
{"id": "b693ece7-b9cb-4114-a518-1fe9dba246e5", "value": "An object fixed to the door or floor to limit the amount a door can open."}
{"id": "3b744dfd-2366-486d-a476-88084a83faae", "value": "A tube for conveying the voice from one room or building to another."}
{"id": "f9e35f76-a9fb-4fe3-9680-811a50ca9841", "value": "An object which is attached to or connected with a door."}

{"id": "ef462eea-6adb-45cf-a4a5-f81a8dd7d9ac", "value": "Objects used to secure buildings, furniture or objects or used in the finishing and (non-structural) decoration of buildings, equipment and furniture."}
{"id": "069eae37-d1db-464b-8f7f-77cdae061168", "value": "A system of communication used in a house to summon servants or on board ship to transmit orders to the engine room."}

{"id": "d6b1272a-92d0-452b-8fbb-8bb28b2d8a17", "value": "A moveable covering, usually to a window, made up of a frame containing slats set at an angle. Allows air to circulate but limits light entering."}
{"id": "3a1817d5-8c8b-4a11-b180-804ae79b1216", "value": "A hole or opening in a ship's hull to allow light and air to enter the vessel, or to aim a weapon through."}
{"id": "a77d7624-be57-45d5-ac8d-b1d861dd5da6", "value": "An object which does not provide light but supports or is attached to lighting equipment."}
{"id": "ce2caea0-38f4-4038-a7c5-8d5645a1c90c", "value": "A rail used to suspend objects from."}
{"id": "59766d5f-fc4b-4d42-bb68-88667f2737fc", "value": "Movable joint attached to fixtures and fittings to enable opening and closure of eg a door."}
{"id": "7ced3fd7-c8e5-424b-a42a-40c69cddc754", "value": "An object which supports or is attached to a curtain."}
{"id": "2f544166-1084-4389-b3b6-7ad3651a7588", "value": "A flat surface designed to hold objects. For a set of shelves use shelving."}
{"id": "459f8ae8-b662-4a92-bab8-06eab922a055", "value": "An object which supports or is attached to a blind."}
{"id": "91d43141-2087-48d1-b5f8-b7d29666372b", "value": "An object which surrounds or makes up a keyhole."}

{"id": "6d9cd6ec-0242-4210-b81a-1305ae312d9c", "value": "A jug that incorporates a practical joke or conundrum into its construction. A combination of cut-outs in the body and hollow handles and tubes render conventional use impossible. The puzzle being to work out how to empty it. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "206d0387-cf8c-4886-b02a-0ace39e5e252", "value": "A stick for agitating milk in a butter churn."}
{"id": "539a4156-ade2-4216-b1bd-0554342fa188", "value": "A curfew with a rounded profile merging into a rounded top, with no discernible angle. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "7b30659c-815e-45c3-a8f5-f0ce6a00de27", "value": "A metal or ceramic cover for an open fire or hearth."}

{"id": "7e6e39cd-70d7-4276-8437-5b84d3176238", "value": "A curfew consisting of a half-bell shape with a raised flange around the cut-away side. A vertical loop handle joins the flange and body. The form is adapted for use against a wall and some are highly decorated. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "4f96b56e-a53b-48d4-894a-91e40e2a6ee4", "value": "A curfew with straight sides flaring outwards from the top. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "dff7bd4a-edbe-470b-9316-4ab237f7f01d", "value": "A necklace or armband made of metal."}
{"id": "4cdfab79-6971-44db-9d85-52a7aa4151a9", "value": "A collection of objects deliberately grouped together and hidden."}
{"id": "e3f9b03a-219b-4413-bdc2-a019f495d2da", "value": "A bracelet or necklace formed by hammering gold onto a triangular-sectioned bar and twisting the metal to form a spiral pattern."}
{"id": "18e3019d-3f91-469c-9b52-89c5bc07cb25", "value": "Material of unknown origin observed adhering to, or found within, an object of another material."}
{"id": "cd03e206-132a-4158-9876-91165d4561b0", "value": "Material derived from living things. Use more specific term where known."}
{"id": "1db8f6fa-ae9f-47e3-8a02-3c59134f59ce", "value": "An indicator of the extent of an area of land."}
{"id": "30ee9cf3-0d66-4035-adb0-64cc62c6207c", "value": "An object used to mark each mile and to indicate distances to locations."}
{"id": "192818cc-bc0d-45cf-8567-27581462a899", "value": "A device used to gauge the speed of a vessel at sea."}

{"id": "6ee68628-f907-4b4e-914a-79a66f4523fa", "value": "An apparatus for weighing, usually consists of a beam on a pivot with a means of supporting the object to be weighed on one side and weights on the other."}
{"id": "622042b8-d992-400b-8d4c-ca1adde05879", "value": "A long graduated staff used in surveying to help measure distance or height."}
{"id": "81c0b3fc-b287-4611-8036-ba1b1e3056ca", "value": "An instrument showing the direction of magnetic north and bearings from it."}
{"id": "f7352ca8-7df1-4e03-ac94-983968efb5ca", "value": "An instrument using lenses to magnify the object being viewed."}
{"id": "8ef3426e-5a5b-422a-839d-3a5fb6995dcb", "value": "An instrument designed to measure temperature."}
{"id": "04afc01e-bd68-404c-affb-452c20b3f234", "value": "A calculating table or frame, specifically one in which balls slide upon wires. Used for the mechanical solution of arithmetical problems."}
{"id": "dec4cea1-8d39-4c5b-8e64-7ad1761cec69", "value": "A graduated vessel or instrument for gauging or measuring the force or quantity of a fluctuating object, such as rainfall, tide, wind etc."}

{"id": "5b33cc10-5ca7-4248-8539-415af7c730f1", "value": "An instrument for establishing the horizontal line of sight and used in surveying. It usually has an eyepiece and an air bubble in a glass tube or dome."}
{"id": "80547310-0e3c-464f-9cd3-72cfe233b260", "value": "An instrument used to measure the passing of time."}
{"id": "5e6cb2ab-35e7-43d7-af64-d0183971a58c", "value": "A scale or index of a sextant, astrolabe or similar instrument."}
{"id": "ec8f1a3d-15a0-4489-a255-7ce5f2f592f2", "value": "An object used to weigh something down or to measure the weight of another object."}

{"id": "a323f1b5-d62b-4817-9196-795aedfa3105", "value": "An instrument for measuring atmospheric pressure by its effects on mercury in a glass tube. It can also be used to measure altitude and depth and is especially used for predicting the weather."}
{"id": "48277503-07fa-4728-a3a6-118f8502fd11", "value": "A piece of wood scored across with notches for the items of an account and then split into halves of which each party kept one."}
{"id": "95928496-91ea-4dff-9a61-44ae56f8101f", "value": "Weight on the end of a graduated line for measuring the depth of water."}
{"id": "09c98f49-96da-431c-a7dd-a694eafe5797", "value": "An instrument for viewing or measuring information on heavenly bodies."}
{"id": "0740e026-2dc0-49ce-aabe-dd617953aa0b", "value": "A rod used to measure the imperial measurements of a pole or a perch."}

{"id": "09c422c3-1bee-479f-b630-867813868523", "value": "A measuring rule used for cloth, with the imperial yard divided into quarters and nails (sixteenths), or using the now obsolete ell of 45 inches."}
{"id": "98f94223-ece1-414a-918b-59c8b7f375b6", "value": "An instrument for measuring height above sea level."}

{"id": "146440b5-837f-41f7-8707-bd6a36b611ec", "value": "Several strands of string twisted together to form a strong thin rope, or thick string, though it has been used in the past as synonomous with rope particularly for ropes on ships."}
{"id": "ad7368b1-00bc-4b1b-a1d3-94bd3cc3d0fc", "value": "A metal thread."}
{"id": "dc77ede0-ce24-40d5-af46-6d8cd1c20a82", "value": "A piece of cast metal obtained from a mould in a form suitable for storage."}
{"id": "b996349c-4d53-4e50-8913-8bce79f7efd0", "value": "A metal collar or cap to strengthen the end of tubes, sticks, shafts, etc. Use with specific object name where known eg spear and ferrule."}
{"id": "94533275-86a0-4d0d-96b0-ef886fac2b9b", "value": "The point or tine of a fork."}
{"id": "0d9ef15a-1336-4893-82d9-c11568dfa201", "value": "The purpose of this object is unknown though it could be for surveying or it could be a charm."}
{"id": "7dfcde1b-ae39-4ebe-aae0-fd69faba01cc", "value": "An object marked or shaped by the pressure of another object upon its surface, whether by deliberate process or unintentionally."}
{"id": "bdc8065b-cb6d-48ce-bf52-ca1ffa8ef498", "value": "A series of connecting metal links."}
{"id": "5a80bac0-ef71-4960-a931-a0b7d15caf4a", "value": "A piece of pointed wood, usually to be driven into the ground."}
{"id": "c005055b-a0d5-4865-bb83-428a2f2f60a1", "value": "A object fitted to an item or garment for the purpose of display or decoration."}
{"id": "48ff354c-fb2d-424e-a2d9-d50c70ae6e47", "value": "A device to limit the amount of liquid coming from a pipe or hole."}

{"id": "4b0f2618-3e02-45e0-b650-12e06ed2bd83", "value": "A slender, cylindrical object. Use specific types of rod where possible. Where it is a rod of material which is part of a production process, eg a glass rod, use rod and enter the material in an object material field."}
{"id": "32ce64f2-f81b-400d-b498-22c3b17022f5", "value": "A clip for marking or holding down pages in a book."}
{"id": "af3c3a84-d004-4831-9475-f95bea69ef03", "value": "A device controlling the passage of liquids or gases."}
{"id": "7d56ac4c-40a4-490e-a064-7596b1488e02", "value": "A deliberate miniaturised replica of an object."}
{"id": "b64e9ce6-ffdd-410f-a646-e6863a0634e8", "value": "Use specific type where known, eg picture frame."}
{"id": "fade9e36-4618-42be-9f0e-005a2a85536c", "value": "A rock carving, especially a prehistoric one."}
{"id": "3fac25a9-7ad6-44fc-8fdc-2a746555697b", "value": "Loose fibres obtained by unpicking old ropes. Mainly used to caulk seams in wooden vessels."}
{"id": "7de3340f-492d-4e5f-ad80-3b893c349b05", "value": "A portable shelter, usually of fabric or leather."}

{"id": "246eb935-adf7-4dca-9684-2e050f1ed5a7", "value": "Ammunition from any period found to have been expended (cannonballs, shells, bullets) which may indicate the possible site of a battle or action on land or at sea. Index where appropriate with Battlefield Debris as a Monument Type."}
{"id": "927f470f-0f26-4c63-a433-395a590b4607", "value": "A tubular orifice to assist in pouring."}
{"id": "74e331d6-3eeb-4251-978e-bd84186b13fe", "value": "A shaped piece of wood that makes up a barrel, key etc."}
{"id": "42024569-603d-4996-ad65-3089ec358c87", "value": "Use specific form where known."}

{"id": "06091996-7e22-495b-b747-3db15fe59125", "value": "A piece of openwork fabric made from twine or cord, either natural fibre or artificial, forming a mesh used for catching birds, animals or fish or for holding other inanimate objects."}
{"id": "73beba3b-a0bf-467c-bf29-14ea87e88923", "value": "Objects which cannot be assigned to any one particular class, or the function of which is unknown."}
{"id": "892a551e-95b4-455a-9ad9-db10ccc225f5", "value": "Use specific type where known."}
{"id": "878fd05f-3bfb-497a-9013-a8d3e3409e5d", "value": "Coiled metal used to give or limit motion."}
{"id": "f4217df5-de6a-45ec-ac02-178c25e7c2a9", "value": "An object showing signs of being worked. Use more specific term where known."}
{"id": "5102ec7c-adb8-4986-b2ae-d1cdcff9fa68", "value": "An item that cannot be identified. Use more specific term, if possible."}
{"id": "4db309db-de14-4786-aa26-13c243fa2f1d", "value": "A three dimensional representation of an object, person or animal."}
{"id": "fc7f08a6-5a52-4057-ab2d-12e97c403f03", "value": "A flat, circular object often made from metal, wood, bone or ivory and of unidentified purpose."}
{"id": "86e5ec6b-1ceb-4f91-88b9-846ced8edb19", "value": "Flint which has been burnt. It is not necessarily worked."}
{"id": "1ae4710f-4ed0-406b-9bf5-d6c13ca151d9", "value": "An object which has one or more holes through it. Use more specific term where known."}
{"id": "baf94e7e-8fc6-473c-a787-bc3d3c013641", "value": "A rod, often of antler, with a hole through it and decorated."}
{"id": "c78b49e7-2319-4632-b867-5aff467dd471", "value": "A length of cord usually made from twisting fibres together which increases the strength of the rope."}
{"id": "02bded81-a81c-4a6f-8547-3e1fd7a599eb", "value": "The part of an object by which it is held when in use, being moved or carried."}
{"id": "e0e54234-2a0d-4645-9931-a9772b36aa22", "value": "Penannular objects of late Bronze Age, usually gold and too small to be worn on arms."}
{"id": "331f2e5a-11e0-4d43-ae3b-4235b434139f", "value": "A portable object of stone, bone, metal or other material featuring a deliberately engraved or incised design."}
{"id": "425a5de0-b718-4c39-bfb1-c8f3f3bcb770", "value": "A projection which can be used to lift or suspend an object, often used as a handle."}
{"id": "f78c9007-0197-4eec-9dd8-60911d8334e4", "value": "A box with one transparent side within which a picture, jewel etc can be displayed."}

{"id": "bfdca094-1734-47fe-a57d-b50becbe4888", "value": "An object used for counting, keeping count or marking the position of a player in a game, usually in the form of a small circular-shaped piece of bone, metal, wood, plastic or other material."}
{"id": "9e9ef628-5246-41f5-9a12-76c8db9f82a9", "value": "An object constructed to allow birds to bathe in it."}
{"id": "3f34de89-3fec-4934-8525-c774ba437e73", "value": "A plug for closing the neck of a container."}
{"id": "5c8b8c24-89f1-4f0a-b22a-b4a42ff4c99e", "value": "An object that commemorates an animal, person, location or event."}
{"id": "f4b1ca8a-08b5-414b-a12c-d49be3e68659", "value": "A cover for an object, usually designed to fit the object."}
{"id": "c5a61af2-7297-428b-9241-802a9a835dde", "value": "A long usually cylindrical object usually made of wood."}
{"id": "7bea5c5b-8919-4be4-a25d-8d22f1732333", "value": "An object to fasten, bind or join one item to another."}
{"id": "22f2866a-82e2-4cbd-914d-401a1a3d442a", "value": "A ball of chalk found on Neolithic sites."}
{"id": "4dfac727-73e6-4369-910f-7d310fcf457a", "value": "An object of Bronze Age date, usually of gold, with an unknown function."}
{"id": "06cb6da5-451c-4d97-b3b2-c80ca63fbfed", "value": "A collection of associated artefacts recovered from a single site."}
{"id": "4c5497bb-1f0d-48b3-97bc-b8c264e14fc1", "value": "A wheel with a series of teeth on its outside which interlock with similar teeth on another cogwheel to receive or give motion."}
{"id": "bcf771f3-cc3d-4d69-92e1-9991a25ca5b1", "value": "An unhewn piece of felled tree, or similar rough mass of wood."}
{"id": "a6f93095-7f00-4b98-b8a2-cb5e70223f7d", "value": "An ornamental tablet of brass. Use a materials thesaurus where brass is a material."}
{"id": "d70a9d3a-145a-4bb8-a5a2-da0f4a056559", "value": "A wood or metal dowel for joining objects together eg for securing roofing slates."}
{"id": "09901fb3-ffa3-4de7-af79-3bb529111659", "value": "A shaped piece of iron perforated for nails and used on horses."}
{"id": "ff5da67d-646d-44cd-810b-96f2d72d39be", "value": "A vessel for keeping the ashes of the dead after cremation."}
{"id": "493afc8c-f1b3-48bb-b64c-ab12baddc9bc", "value": "A vessel consisting of three small pots joined, often on a hollow ring, at the base."}
{"id": "c61af407-6ee4-466c-a315-a4615f82b309", "value": "A projectile discharged from a weapon, usually a firearm."}
{"id": "196b4276-76a7-4a8c-90a5-b0dea5f3a202", "value": "Weight used for weighing specific quantities and qualities of gold."}

{"id": "1af5d18c-005a-47e3-b178-871ea3bae6ae", "value": "An axehead of early Bronze Age date, made of copper or bronze, which is flat on both sides and generally lacks side flanges or other hafting aids."}

{"id": "0ee7eaee-153c-4ad5-93e6-83bac149b64b", "value": "A form of axehead where the body is hollow allowing for insertion of the haft. Usually bronze or iron and of late Bronze Age or Iron Age date. Most examples feature a side loop to further assist hafting."}

{"id": "3253f74e-99bc-4f74-8acc-de49d9604348", "value": "A stone axe in which the surface is fully covered by negative removals. Core axes may be made on flakes and have part of the flake's original surface but this cannot be part of the edge otherwise use FLAKED AXE. (Source: SARC)"}
{"id": "3a9d3b38-6288-4992-a3a2-4efeea8d24ba", "value": "An axehead of flint or other stone commonly used for Neolithic types."}

{"id": "d7def807-f281-429a-a943-5ff7127c527f", "value": "A bronze axehead of middle or late Bronze Age date in which the side flanges and the bar/stop on both faces are connected, forming a single hafting aid. For palstaves with side loops use looped palstave."}

{"id": "909b0825-9f66-4471-a772-15c78e2105f7", "value": "A bronze axehead of earlier Bronze Age date the sides of which are raised, either by casting or hammering, to form flanges on both faces which aid hafting. Some types also feature a raised bar or stop between the flanges."}

{"id": "2e436aa8-d765-472a-abba-da11161fd96e", "value": "A form of bronze axehead of middle or late Bronze Age date in which narrow, high flanges on both faces are hammered over to enclose the axe haft. Some types feature a side loop to further assist hafting."}
{"id": "b25d504c-45d0-4e24-8534-42b8f9686873", "value": "An axehead of flint or other stone, commonly used for Neolithic types."}

{"id": "0594f883-75a9-4c47-b209-db0777daf541", "value": "The cutting or chopping part of an axe; bifacially worked, longitudinal section symmetrical, cutting edge parallel to the direction of the hafted tool as swung."}
{"id": "8e34b1c4-4a6c-4210-bef0-14c37233f7ff", "value": "A chisel ended flaked axehead common in the Mesolithic."}
{"id": "596d938f-24b4-42ec-b096-6da3b604a58f", "value": "A small doll controlled by the operators hand either directly or with strings."}
{"id": "6ff9e188-16d8-4dac-850a-1a547002bee0", "value": "A container for the storage of tobacco."}
{"id": "d3a16933-ec01-405d-bda9-a840379784c8", "value": "A pouch for containing tobacco."}
{"id": "0a28a55d-49de-41bc-a7b6-2495184f797c", "value": "A small bar raised or lowered by a latchlifter which is used to fasten gates or doors etc."}
{"id": "a647eff8-81ed-4015-833e-491d8bdc9c0b", "value": "A belt used to confine a hawk's wings."}
{"id": "d182db59-a80d-4a26-8a76-6c1d72df9fe6", "value": "A mowing implement with a large curved blade and a long handle."}

{"id": "e91f10c3-49cf-4e56-a621-e0c3469098e3", "value": "The cutting or chopping part of an adze; bifacially worked, longitudinal section symmetrical, cutting edge parallel to the direction of the hafted tool as swung."}

{"id": "4c83c279-95f8-4b18-87ac-e9233b3048c4", "value": "A jug with a roughly cylindrical or slightly flaring lower body, a pronounced inward-sloping shoulder and a marked neck/body angle. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "8a1ccdb4-7f64-4556-be2e-6e9e9ce963de", "value": "A jug with a constriction between the upper and lower body sections. (Source: MPRG)"}

{"id": "3eed5742-88e6-436f-bb37-78efc9bea7e2", "value": "A jug form which usually has a short, narrow neck and rim and an applied spout. The spout is usually tubular and free standing, or attached to the rim/neck, rising from just above the high shoulder or girth. (Source: MPRG)"}

{"id": "7668e247-d4f8-429d-ac16-38981bbd42be", "value": "A type of stoneware jug dating to the 16th and 17th centuries, popularly known as a Bellarmine jug, shaped in the figure of a bearded man. They were produced in the Cologne region, particularly Frechen."}
{"id": "d396990b-0eb6-4ed3-b9e7-5f071bbc5fb4", "value": "A container for holding or pouring liquids, usually having a handle or lip."}
{"id": "281b699a-310f-4695-9804-e0442fc7f2eb", "value": "A type of jug decorated with applied figures in the form of knights in armour. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "4d11240f-568a-47cc-b211-ebabaaf19d3c", "value": "A jug with a body profile resembling two cones joined together at their widest points, producing a distinct carination. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "6ae033e0-ca13-4b19-a5fe-be58035d44bc", "value": "A jug with straight vertical sides and roughly equal rim and base diameters. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "27beb2e4-bad8-42a0-94a3-2858081dab43", "value": "A jug with little or no discernible neck and an even, convex profile form rim to base, which are roughly equal in diameter. (Source: MPRG)"}

{"id": "64113475-7270-4181-b6e8-c7bd77cbbb6e", "value": "A jug with an evenly rounded profile and a discernible basal angle; the maximum diameter is near the mid point and in the upper half of the vessel. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "10edcb05-65ba-4c4d-841e-c941fa3924e3", "value": "A jug with a maximum diameter in the lower half of the vessel and with no discernible shoulder. (Source: MPRG)"}

{"id": "adeea8d2-6a0e-43c7-9af5-9fe6e18b6b89", "value": "A jug with a pierced bunghole just above the base. the bunghole can be made through an applied knob or disc of clay, or simply a hole in the vessel wall. In use, the hole would probably have had a tap or spigot attached. (Source: MPRG)"}

{"id": "b2563b4a-afd6-4ad3-80f9-567416a6d259", "value": "A jug form characterized by the addition of three applied feet. The feet are usually short and stubby. Double index with the appropriate profile type. (Source: MPRG)"}

{"id": "60037896-9c89-429d-8190-f8b88ac3df09", "value": "Any type of jug with decoration representing the form of a human face or figure. The shape of the vessel often forms the outline of the human face or figure. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "fcc83063-597f-4dd5-a6bc-ea668578da60", "value": "A jug with a rounded profile and a rounded base, i.e. with no discernible basal angle. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "9efb12e6-04fc-4f1f-8837-2ba70aae5cdb", "value": "A jug with more or less straight sides that flare out from a narrow rim or neck to a wider base. (Source: MPRG)"}

{"id": "019a7c09-ee00-485c-ad18-9656557c0b45", "value": "A jug with a sinuous profile where the rim, girth and base are of roughly equal diameter, and the neck and lower body are narrower.(Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "b9e53874-d679-4ef4-831c-ff92acc893c8", "value": "An instrument for writing or drawing with ink."}
{"id": "f6b0f097-e7ac-4259-9909-25053a9a00a9", "value": "A plate on which an offering is made."}

{"id": "5c38c308-dfed-49e3-9511-6de1dadad001", "value": "A vessel composed of three or more separate compartments, joined together and pierced to allow liquid to flow from one to another. There may be one or more handles. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "94dbe94e-e397-416c-8eb1-31977ae4aadb", "value": "A stone used for sharpening edged tools, knives etc."}
{"id": "ac5eb61b-432e-468f-b41a-4f31a0b2a921", "value": "A religious cloth often used to cover coffins."}
{"id": "b396d6fd-81c0-4d2a-813e-4be2e054701f", "value": "An item with both secular and religious signifigance."}
{"id": "60a739e6-0741-45d7-bc31-994feaaa1ad1", "value": "An Egyptian religious statuette."}
{"id": "eeb54ef5-f751-48d2-ad84-c01ceeea95b7", "value": "An object for making an offering to a deity. It includes objects concerned with curses, sacrifices, and prayers and their related objects."}
{"id": "592c6586-7bf0-452b-ae76-5dd0e1e48d34", "value": "Polished stone balls interpreted as ritual objects in the Scottish Iron Age."}
{"id": "bb8b4d9d-0900-433d-a8fb-425eb1aac72c", "value": "A flail used for the mortification of the flesh."}
{"id": "3d6fd6e0-2870-4881-acdb-a32f1853b33c", "value": "A container for holding water that has been blessed by a priest and is used for symbolic rituals of purification."}
{"id": "cb8a0ba7-63c0-4372-817c-beca6e71ca06", "value": "A vessel to contain the wafers used in the Eucharist."}
{"id": "688cff53-4d40-46c4-9d09-fd4d73ce5ea4", "value": "A container used upon the altar."}
{"id": "30943945-4516-4679-83c8-9b219e88393b", "value": "Objects concerned with marriage and weddings."}
{"id": "a1b319b5-2d94-40d5-9b1e-90c8eed0dc59", "value": "An object related to deaths, burials or funerals."}
{"id": "5412097f-3bcf-4c53-815e-9d07862b8e9c", "value": "A tablet with a handle fitted to the back of it."}
{"id": "4893754a-3818-4cb4-b858-b4bfc4ac5278", "value": "A flag or object depicting a symbolic representation carried as part of a religious ceremony."}
{"id": "a82364df-ec23-42cc-895a-ede3c34f36a3", "value": "An object carried about the person for religious purposes."}
{"id": "be2742fd-f6db-4ee9-88be-6db09b99b9de", "value": "An object used within a divinational process."}
{"id": "1c4b9d11-1392-4493-8d16-f05f61f76dee", "value": "Use for structural objects within or connected to a place of worship, eg font. For structures, use a monuments thesaurus."}
{"id": "1e6fc2fc-93e3-4fb2-a6be-284dfbd0e91d", "value": "A figure, representation or image, which is itself regarded as sacred."}
{"id": "f8783f8d-410e-4172-a55b-68f5dbc54259", "value": "An object used in the Eucharist."}
{"id": "e9323ee5-0ae9-4500-a558-585778bb6b4c", "value": "Tongs used with incense."}
{"id": "c2b1746a-b511-460f-ac35-f4213075ce6a", "value": "A small spoon used with incense."}
{"id": "2e55c552-d895-412c-ab66-5ee4fc1aa4cf", "value": "Objects used or associated with religious, ritual or funerary activities."}
{"id": "e0c04a98-7277-4fc7-8e44-026a29e90c1d", "value": "An ancient Egyptian gem cut in the shape of a scarab beetle and engraved with symbols on its flat side."}
{"id": "db0bdb1f-4efe-41a6-ada4-8bac00caa837", "value": "The staff or crook of a bishop or abbot."}
{"id": "12752b15-dd5b-4eda-b12f-22570c361fe8", "value": "A small shovel used with incense."}
{"id": "4f989818-5ad1-421b-819e-d8a417f1e7cf", "value": "A brush or perforated ball on a handle used to sprinkle holy water."}
{"id": "11900ae0-5b29-4d23-acb5-9a6aec8535e4", "value": "A bowl used in magical ceremonies."}
{"id": "88173cbc-da21-4d28-bbaa-dc1f07cb7dda", "value": "An object in the shape of an Egyptian dung beetle, used to symbolise the motive power of the sun. Use specific term where known."}
{"id": "aff903a6-77c0-42a0-b5d6-68b128814528", "value": "An image of a deity used as a focus for worship, usually used for non Christian images."}
{"id": "c35ff3eb-c661-4ca9-907d-f77211cb04ff", "value": "A figurative or decorative object made of corn, used as a charm for luck or to ward off evil spirits."}
{"id": "2f477670-238e-4e25-8a0e-12608e949bcf", "value": "An object fashioned in the image of a penis."}
{"id": "1989ffbd-490f-4b4e-b1e0-ebb3a15c435b", "value": "A stone inscribed or marked with ogham letters used for a memorial"}
{"id": "da865087-5b58-4dd3-9049-e87fb393aea6", "value": "An object consisting of a vertical member with a transverse member. Usually there is a religious or ritual significance to such an object."}
{"id": "5810b9bf-d0e1-426b-9c94-6b7f9cb2bb3f", "value": "Equipment used to perform circumcision."}
{"id": "8651c3f5-f8e7-46ab-befb-0da6d03a1cf3", "value": "A shrine often including representations of a god or gods or other holy relics which could be carried by worshippers whilst travelling."}
{"id": "9a74fd87-251e-496b-81ac-ba0b331d9402", "value": "A vessel containing a religious oil or unguent."}
{"id": "19cf32ff-e07c-430d-ac5b-06b9224bf334", "value": "An object representing the sun, made of bronze or gold usually dating from the European Bronze Age."}
{"id": "5ce9b526-e810-4ea9-a4d8-0e4945fd5a61", "value": "Wind-blown sand."}
{"id": "bdea6fb2-675d-45e6-b696-21d575eafa10", "value": "A thin scoop used for cleaning the ear."}
{"id": "8a6d3dd3-fc44-4ce9-afa4-ef0059d01e04", "value": "A specialised fitting for Roman armour. For a part of a garment use APRON."}

{"id": "90911e78-c702-473f-b73c-28f728ea81cb", "value": "Roughly spherical, > 5 \u00b5m, soot particles produced from the incomplete combustion of fossil fuels. Used as an indicator of industrialisation, and can also be used as a dating tool."}
{"id": "2f645a97-d521-4659-884d-42a4975b302e", "value": "Waste flakes and cores produced in the manufacture of stone implements."}

{"id": "916811de-2bf9-4ffd-ac74-923d9e39a265", "value": "A flint blade with negative impressions of removals on one side of the dorsal surface, creating a crest. These constitute part of a previously worked striking platfom or result from preparing the flaked surface on a core before detaching flakes or blades."}
{"id": "950e8c66-69f4-4d1b-a044-5ed48de6326d", "value": "A struck piece of flint or other stone where the length is at least twice the width."}

{"id": "11d5af05-0512-441e-af8b-79c249fba195", "value": "A jar adapted by the addition of two handles. Handles may be horizontal or vertical loops or horizontal or curved lugs.
